<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-13T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-13T19:00:00-05:00" n="433" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2531/355a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-13T20:00:00-04:00">September
                                    13, 1939—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>118. Following conversations regarding which you are being informed by
                            air pouch, a basis has been agreed upon with Gazitua for announcement of
                            trade-agreement negotiations with Chile, possibly in about 3 weeks. It
                            is understood that the proposed basis has been submitted to his
                            Government for consideration.</p>
                        <p>The basis leaves the exchange control question open for discussion in the
                            light of the Chilean situation at the time of negotiations.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>